<!--
VOICING PLAN — 4152 Thou, Who at Thy First Eucharist (D major)
Key: D, 2 sharps (F#, C#). Hymn is rich in ii-V-I and vi sequences.

Phrases 1-2 (mm.1-6 + 7-9): I/ii alternation mirrors each repeat.
  "334" open LH for D, "333" for V7 (A7) with all 4 tones.
  Arpeggiated LH in mm.3,9 — passing texture between block changes.
  Vi (Bm) in m.8 replaces literal repeat for color.

Inner section (mm.10-15): G-Em-F#m-A sequential motion. Full 4-note LH
  throughout. RH doubles inner voices. Contrary motion LH descends while
  RH ascends to climax.

Climax + cadence (mm.13-18): High D5 in m.13, full spread G/Bm in m.14.
  Stepwise descent mm.15-18: A7→D→A7→Bm→G→Em→D→A7→D. Final I all
  sustained with pedal D2 grounding the resolution.

VOICE LEADING: The C#4 in the A7 chords resolves upward to D4 in I —
  leading tone motion preserved across every dominant-tonic pair.

TEXTURE ARC: Light 2-note RH opens, builds to full 4-voice LH at climax
  (m.14), resolves to sustained final chord.
-->
